The coming weeks and months tackling police reform are very important. We’ll need to listen to each other, work together, and act together. @RepPeteStauber and I joined @realDonaldTrump at the @WhiteHouse for a big first step. 

Congress, we’re up next. https://t.co/ySlrS8EQJV

full_text: In the coming days, I will be working on pragmatic solutions and introducing legislation to ensure more accountability and transparency within police departments while helping our law enforcement officers to safely perform their jobs. (3/3)

full_text: One hundred years ago today, Elias Clayton, Elmer Jackson and Isaac McGhie were falsely accused of a crime they didn’t commit and lynched by a mob in Duluth. As we reflect on the ugliest day in Duluth’s history, I will continue to pray for healing across the nation. (1/2)

That’s why I introduced legislation to require federal agencies to purchase drugs made in the USA & reduce dependence on nations like China. retweeted_text: A bipartisan (and socially distanced) flight to DC this morning to vote on Coronavirus economic relief. @RepPeteStauber @RepAngieCraig @BettyMcCollum04 https://t.co/8o48sSvYrW

full_text:
Last night, the Senate approved an economic relief bill to help American families and businesses impacted by COVID-19.

I look forward to doing my part and helping to pass this bill out of the House later this week.

Read my full statement, here: https://t.co/YnHcyfHMHt

Neighbors helping neighbors.
Communities supporting small businesses.
People lending a hand to others.

In the toughest of times, Americans rise to the occasion. We are in #InItTogether!

full_text:
As the coronavirus pandemic continues to unfold, the entire Minnesota Delegation wanted to address all of you in one unified voice. Our message is this:

No challenge is too great for America to overcome. We will get through this too-- together. https://t.co/UeAvkgYSrZ

All Americans want a cleaner environment.  Planting one trillion trees would remove roughly two thirds of all man-made carbon produced since the industrial revolution.

🌲 Let's rise to that challenge.🌲 #TrillionTreesAct https://t.co/iZIFdm2MWH

full_text: I was proud to speak at a press conference in support of the Trillion Trees Act. By setting the goal of planting one trillion trees globally by 2050, we are taking the necessary steps to naturally sequester carbon AND invest in our forest product industry! https://t.co/utvWEua0KT

My latest interview with @RepPeteStauber, who represents Iron Range cities and Duluth in Minnesota's 8th Congressional District: https://t.co/G3qqLxFFZY #MNPol

"We have to remove the stigma of having a mental health crisis or mental health issue. We have to remove the stigma."

full_text: Today, I requested unanimous consent for the Born-Alive Abortion Survivors Protection Act. Sadly, Democrats once again refused to consider a bill that would require physicians to give lifesaving medical care to babies that survive an abortion. https://t.co/wgM0cQRlkv

retweeted_text: Thank you to @RepAndyBiggsAZ, @Rep_Hunter, @RepMattGaetz, @RepSeanDuffy, @RepDustyJohnson, @PeteStauber & @RepJohnJoyce for visiting #DEA in Arizona and learning about the drug threat facing the Southwest Border and our country. https://t.co/HHc8hmHytg

full_text: Every yr, thousands of pounds of illegal drugs come into the U.S. through the southern border. During our briefing w/the DEA, we were shown confiscated fentanyl, enough to kill 11 million people. We must recognize that our porous borders are tied to the drug crisis. https://t.co/or9g3FadKQ

retweeted_text: Making sure our schools work for every student is something we can all agree on. I’m proud to work across the aisle with fellow Minnesotan @RepPeteStauber to introduce the #IDEAFullFundingAct, which increase special education funding across Minnesota.

full_text: I spoke in honor of World Down Syndrome Day, which was March 21st. One of the greatest blessings in my life is my 16-year old son Isaac, who has Down Syndrome. I was happy to speak about the value and joy that individuals like Isaac bring to the world: https://t.co/bKA9RM6jp2

Today is #LawEnforcementAppreciationDay.  Thank you to all law enforcers who train hard to keep us safe every day. 

#USArmy photo by Pat Molnar https://t.co/BMSdHleXDt

full_text: The absence of strong border security encourages illegal immigration, human trafficking, & the spread of illicit drugs. As a law enforcement officer of 23 yrs, I know that Minnesotans want a nation of law and order. It is time to secure our border & keep the American people safe.
